// testing.legendCreator.builder.json — Legend Creator builder UI (window chrome + canvas control
// + the block-row/group-card/layout-bar/palette sub-controls it composes).
// Files: Source/Lemoine/Controls/Legend/LemoineLegendBuilder.xaml.cs (canvas, palette drag/drop,
//        block editor, bulk editor, footer counts, templates popup),
//        Source/Lemoine/Testing/LegendCreator/LegendSettingsWindow.xaml.cs (host window: title bar,
//        tabs, title/subtitle popup, sizing, text styles, create/update, status flash),
//        Source/Lemoine/Controls/Legend/LemoineLegendBlockRow.xaml.cs (one swatch+label block row),
//        Source/Lemoine/Controls/Legend/LemoineLegendGroupCard.xaml.cs (a group card of block rows),
//        Source/Lemoine/Controls/Legend/LemoineLegendLayoutBar.xaml.cs (top ribbon: legend pill +
//        title/subtitle edit popup),
//        Source/Lemoine/Controls/Legend/LemoineLegendPalette.xaml.cs (source palette: scope pills,
//        trade dropdown, filter list).
// LemoineLegendPreview.xaml.cs was reviewed and has NO hardcoded display text — every TextBlock it
// renders reads live from LegendLayoutConfig/LegendGroupConfig/LegendBlockConfig (Title, Subtitle,
// group title, block name), so there is nothing to externalize there.
// NOTE: the run-log lines for LegendCreatorEventHandler.cs live in testing.legendCreator.json —
// this file is display/UI text only, no overlap. Kept in code: shape-kind tokens ("square"/"solid")
// persisted on LegendBlockConfig, the standard imperial view-scale ladder (ImperialScales array —
// data, not prose, mirrors Revit's own scale dropdown), the "✕"/"＋"/"↑"/"↓"/"˅"/"✎"/"×" standalone
// icon glyphs and the Segoe MDL2 trash glyph (ConvertFromUtf32), and internal Tag markers
// ("deleteBtn"). Icon glyphs baked into a translated label (e.g. "＋  Add New Group") stay inline
// with the text, matching the established clashDefinitions.json convention. Also kept: the "All"
// scope token compared against LemoineLegendPalette._scope (internal state, not display) — only
// the label text passed to MakeScopePill for that same pill is externalized.
